== 七、易混介词短语辨析精选

#warn(title: "in the end vs at the end")[
  #hl[in the end] = #cn-hl[最终、最后] (时间,= finally)
  #example(([#hl[In the end], we decided to go.]))
  #hl[at the end (of)] = #cn-hl[在……的末尾] (具体位置)
  #example(([#hl[At the end] of the film, they marry.]))
]

#warn(title: "in time vs on time")[
  #hl[on time] = #cn-hl[准时] (按计划)
  #example(([The train arrived #hl[on time].]))
  #hl[in time] = #cn-hl[及时] (赶得上,来得及)
  #example(([We got there #hl[in time] for dinner.]))
]

#warn(title: "made of vs made from")[
  #hl[made of] —— 强调成品仍可识别为该材料
  #example(([a desk #hl[made of] wood (木头桌子,看得见木纹)]))
  #hl[made from] —— 强调原料经过加工成为成品，原形通常不再明显
  #example(([Paper is #hl[made from] wood. (纸是木头造的,看不出木)]))
  这不是严格的“物理变化/化学变化”测试，而是说话者如何看待材料与成品的关系。
]

#warn(title: "by vs until (复习)")[
  #hl[by] = 截止期限 (不迟于) —— #hl[Submit by Friday.]
  #hl[until] = 持续到 (一直到) —— #hl[Wait until Friday.]
]

== 八、介词动词与短语动词

必须区分后接补语的介词和没有自身补语的小品词：

#example((
  [look #hl[after] the child —— #en[after] 引出补语，是介词动词],
  [turn #hl[off] the light / turn the light #hl[off] —— #en[off] 是可移动的小品词],
  [look #hl[up to] her —— #en[up] 是小品词，#en[to] 是介词],
))

空间联想有时有助记忆，但短语动词已经高度惯例化，不能只凭图像预测：

#table(
  columns: (1fr, 1fr, 1fr),
  align: (left, left, left),
  stroke: 0.5pt + c-line,
  inset: 7pt,
  table.cell(fill: c-soft2)[*短语*],
  table.cell(fill: c-soft2)[*含义*],
  table.cell(fill: c-soft2)[*透明度与学习方法*],
  [#hl[look up to]],
  [尊敬],
  [联系较透明：向上看 → 仰望；仍按整体搭配记忆],
  [#hl[look down on]],
  [轻视],
  [联系较透明：俯视可引出轻蔑],
  [#hl[put off]],
  [推迟],
  [部分可理解，但“推迟”是固定词汇义],
  [#hl[put up with]],
  [忍受],
  [不透明：不要编造空间故事，整体记忆],
  [#hl[come across]],
  [偶遇],
  [部分可理解：路径与偶然相遇有关],
  [#hl[run into]],
  [撞见],
  [部分可理解：接触义延伸为偶遇],
  [#hl[get over]],
  [克服],
  [联系较透明：越过障碍],
  [#hl[break down]],
  [崩溃/分解],
  [多义且部分词汇化；结合具体宾语学习],
  [#hl[turn out]],
  [结果是],
  [不透明：整体记忆],
  [#hl[give up]],
  [放弃],
  [高度词汇化：整体记忆],
)

#principle[
  先判断小品词还是介词，再在完整句块中学习宾语位置和意义。图像可以辅助记忆，但不能代替真实用法。\

  #en[look down on] 的“向下看→轻视”联系较透明；#en[put up with] 等表达则更固定，应整体记忆。
]

== 九、IELTS 应用句型

下列句型展示关系表达，不应机械套用。写作时要保证比较对象和逻辑关系准确：

#callout(body-color: c-soft2, border-color: c-primary, icon: "🎯")[
  #text(weight: "bold", fill: c-primary)[Task 1 图表描述]
  #v(0.3em)
  #example((
    [Sales increased #hl[by] 30%, #hl[from] 100 #hl[to] 130 units, #hl[between] 2010 #hl[and] 2020.],
    [#hl[In contrast to] the rise recorded in the previous year, the figure fell.],
    [The figure #hl[for] the third category remained stable.],
  ))
]

#callout(body-color: c-soft2, border-color: c-primary, icon: "🎯")[
  #text(weight: "bold", fill: c-primary)[Task 2 议论文]
  #v(0.3em)
  #example((
    [#hl[With regard to] education funding, many people argue #hl[in favor of] reducing tuition fees.],
    [#hl[In spite of] the drawbacks, the benefits outweigh them.],
    [#hl[In terms of] long-term impact, this policy is crucial #hl[for] sustainable development.],
    [#hl[For the benefit of] future generations, governments should act now.],
  ))
]

#v(1em)

#tip[
  IELTS 写作中，一小组高频介词会反复出现:
  #formula[in / of / by / from / to / for / on / with / despite / in terms of]
  优先掌握它们表达的关系和常见句块，比堆叠生僻短语更可靠。
]
